        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 4:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 16
miles southwest of Higbee, or 28 miles south of North La Junta,
moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Higbee.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
